@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

title Write-Ahead Log Operation

' [step1 {"name":"Initial State"}]
actor Client
participant "KVStore Server" as KVStore
database "Write-Ahead Log\nwal.log" as WAL
database "In-Memory State" as MemStore

note over WAL #E6F3FF
**Existing Log Entries**
Set(K1,V1) - Index 1
Set(K2,V2) - Index 2
Set(K3,V3) - Index 3
end note

note over MemStore #E6F3FF
**Current Visible State**
Key1: Value1
Key2: Value2
Key3: Value3
end note
' [/step1]

' [step2 {"name":"Client Write Request"}]
Client -> KVStore : Set(K4,V4)
activate KVStore

note over KVStore #FFFFCC
**Core Rule**
Durability before visibility
end note
' [/step2]

' [step3 {"name":"Append to WAL", "newPage":"true"}]
KVStore -> WAL : 1. Append Set(K4,V4) with Index 4
activate WAL
note right of WAL #FFE6E6
**Durability Step**
• Append to the log
• Force fsync() to disk
end note
WAL --> KVStore : Append confirmed
deactivate WAL
' [/step3]

' [step4 {"name":"Update Memory"}]
KVStore -> MemStore : 2. Update K4 = V4
activate MemStore
note right of MemStore #E6FFE6
**Visibility Step**
• Update in-memory state
• Key4 is now visible
• Safe because WAL is durable
end note
MemStore --> KVStore : Update confirmed
deactivate MemStore
' [/step4]

' [step5 {"name":"Success Response"}]
KVStore --> Client : Success
deactivate KVStore

note over KVStore, MemStore #E6F3FF
**Recovery Guarantee**
If the server crashes after the WAL write but before the memory update,
the operation can be replayed during startup recovery.
end note
' [/step5]

@enduml
